# CRM UI and Developer Experience Standards

## UI Stack and Component Rules
- Use `Tailwind CSS` and `shadcn/ui` patterns consistently.
- Build and reuse shared UI in `packages/ui`.
- Avoid one-off custom components when a shadcn-based composition fits.
- Keep design language consistent across `crm` and `partner-portal`.
- Support dark mode from day one in all new UI work.

## Next.js Component Strategy
- Default to Server Components.
- Use `"use client"` only when required by interactivity/browser-only APIs.
- When a client component is used, keep client boundary minimal.

## Product UX Expectations
- UX must be polished, professional, and consistent for internal and partner users.
- Forms and mutations should include clear validation, loading, and error states.
- Use shared primitives and patterns to reduce UX drift between apps.

## Developer Experience and Maintainability
- Optimize for easy module onboarding and long-term scale.
- New pages/routes should follow established folder and naming conventions.
- New APIs must include typed contracts and authorization checks.
- New permissions and RBAC entries should be easy to register and reuse.

## First-Phase Feature Priorities
- Prioritize:
  - CRM dashboard
  - Partner dashboard
  - Organization/partner management
  - Partner profile management + validation requests
  - Inventory module foundations and extensible module architecture
